Optimizing blue hour photos📸🔵

1. Shoot at blue hour, 45-30 minutes before sunrise or 30-45 minutes after sunset

2. Add a light in frame to help set the mood that its either dusk or dawn

3. Include a human element to show that it’s getting dark or the sun is rising & that person is awake early

4. Shoot at a lower F stop so you can keep your shutter speed at a decent setting so you the movement isn’t blurred

How to Avoid with creator Burnout🔴😳

Let’s face it we’ve all been there at least once🙃

I know I faced it more than once in 2022, here are my best tips for avoiding & overcoming burnout

1. Take BREAKS

Obvious right? Not not so much sometimes, when you are in a constant state of stress thinking everything has to get done this day. Sometimes it doesn’t, & taking a 20 minute break will not destroy your path to reaching your goals

2. Seek Support

Friends, family, or Significant others are great people to confide in. It’s as simple as ranting to them about how you feel or just someone to hang with to take your mind off of work

3. Prioritize Better 

This one is an important one. Think about it this way. What will happen if task 1 isn’t finished today? I won’t get paid for the job. Ok that’s a high priority task. What if you don’t do task 2 today? Deadline isn’t til Friday. Task 2 becomes secondary to task one, so forget about it a bit to focus on what’s in front of you

4. Set Boundaries 

Set boundaries for social media time, time spent working, time spent watching Netflix. Without written boundaries for yourself what’s stopping you from spending 8 hours mindlessly scrolling & getting too many hits of dopamine in a day

5. Journal

This one is one im starting this year. Maybe even a few sentences is all you need. The reason this can help is if you write the things you did on Dec 3 2022, & you were feeling good. Then today you aren’t feeling good. Maybe you should reflect on the choices & decisions you’ve been making today?

Last year, I had at least 3 creator burnouts that I can remember & they weren’t fun. The best way to avoid them is to take preventable measures
